The paper deals with action recognition using recurrent neural networks, specifically LSTMs, and proposes a new architecture called DDLSTM that can learn temporal dependencies from two domains concurrently. This makes it likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The datasets used in the evaluation are related to multimedia (cs.MM), and the paper proposes a new method for learning and alignment, which could also fall under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
